# Layout & Navigation Architecture

## Layout structure

```
BackofficeLayout (BackofficeLayout.tsx)
├── LayoutContext.Provider  — shares { sidebarCollapsed, toggleSidebar }
├── AppHeader               — fixed, h-14, z-50, bg-gray-900
│   ├── Brand (logo link)
│   └── UserMenu (Avatar + DropdownMenu logout)
├── AppSidebar              — fixed left-0 top-14, dark bg-gray-900
│   ├── All NavModules as a vertical list
│   │   ├── CollapsedModuleRow  (icon-only when w-[60px])
│   │   ├── DirectNavRow        (module has 1 child)
│   │   ├── AccordionModuleRow  (module has 2+ children, Collapsible)
│   │   └── FlyoutModuleRow     (module.flyout === true → chevron-right)
│   └── CollapseToggle button
├── MegaMenuPanel           — fixed overlay right of sidebar (only when flyout active)
└── <main>                  — flex-1, ml-60 (or ml-[60px] collapsed), Outlet
```

## navConfig — the single source of truth

File: `apps/backoffice-web/src/components/layout/navConfig.ts`

### Type hierarchy

```ts
NavModule        // one entry = one row in the sidebar
  .id            // unique string key
  .label         // Vietnamese display name
  .icon          // lucide-react ComponentType
  .defaultPath   // navigate here when collapsed or when module tab is clicked
  .flyout?       // true → renders MegaMenuPanel instead of accordion
  .sections[]    // NavSection[]

NavSection       // collapsible group (shown in accordion or mega-menu column)
  .id
  .label?        // optional group heading (uppercase, shown in accordion/mega-menu)
  .children[]    // NavChild[]

NavChild         // individual route link
  .to            // route path
  .label         // Vietnamese link text
  .end?          // pass to NavLink `end` prop (exact match)
  .icon?         // optional lucide icon shown beside the label
```

### Adding a new top-level module

```ts
// In navConfig.ts, add to the navConfig array:
{
  id: "accounting",
  label: "Kế toán",
  icon: BookOpen,
  defaultPath: "/accounting/journals",
  sections: [
    {
      id: "accounting-main",
      children: [
        { to: "/accounting/journals",  label: "Nhật ký kế toán", icon: FileText },
        { to: "/accounting/accounts",  label: "Tài khoản",       icon: Layers },
      ],
    },
  ],
},
```

No other files need to change — the sidebar reads navConfig automatically.

### Adding children to an existing module

```ts
// Add a child to an existing section:
{ to: "/inventory/stock-take", label: "Kiểm kê kho", icon: ClipboardList }

// Or add a new named section to an existing module:
{
  id: "inventory-returns",
  label: "TRẢ HÀNG",
  children: [
    { to: "/inventory/returns", label: "Phiếu trả hàng", icon: CornerUpLeft },
  ],
}
```

### Adding a flyout module (like Danh mục)

```ts
{
  id: "my-flyout",
  label: "My Flyout",
  icon: Grid,
  defaultPath: "/admin/my-entity",
  flyout: true,             // ← this triggers MegaMenuPanel
  sections: [
    {
      id: "group-a",
      label: "NHÓM A",       // uppercase heading in the mega-menu column
      children: [
        { to: "/admin/entity-a", label: "Thực thể A" },
      ],
    },
  ],
},
```

